Cindy's decided to bring her father
back to Columbus.

01:13:19.978 --> 01:13:22.313
That's where my support network is now.

01:13:22.481 --> 01:13:23.481
It's home.

01:13:25.484 --> 01:13:30.822
My only concern is that
that may not be what Leo wants.

01:13:30.989 --> 01:13:33.366
Yeah, I already talked to him about it.

01:13:33.534 --> 01:13:35.118
He seemed to like the idea.

01:13:35.285 --> 01:13:38.788
I understand that, Cindy. But, uh...

01:13:38.956 --> 01:13:42.250
...you know, you haven't
seen Leo in a long time...

01:13:42.418 --> 01:13:45.128
...and he's battling dementia now.

01:13:45.295 --> 01:13:49.257
So it kind of puts me
in a tough position here, you know?

01:13:49.425 --> 01:13:51.634
Yeah, I understand.

01:13:51.802 --> 01:13:56.973
But seeing that she is the presumed
guardian, we hope to avoid litigation.

01:13:57.141 --> 01:14:00.518
So do I. And I know that we can.
Absolutely.

01:14:00.686 --> 01:14:03.604
We definitely can.

01:14:03.772 --> 01:14:07.608
Now, I'm sorry,
but I actually have to see another client.

01:14:08.986 --> 01:14:12.155
But we should set up another time
to talk about this, definitely, okay?

01:14:12.322 --> 01:14:13.781
Yes.

01:14:14.366 --> 01:14:15.867
Okay.

01:14:26.253 --> 01:14:28.504
Is it that bad?
Yeah, it's that bad.

01:14:28.672 --> 01:14:30.840
Take her to court. You'll kill her.
I can't.

01:14:31.008 --> 01:14:34.010
What do you mean? She's a mess.
You're a pillar of the community.

01:14:34.178 --> 01:14:38.389
I just can't go back in front of Judge Lee.
It'll look very bad. Trust me.

01:14:38.557 --> 01:14:41.851
I can't afford that right now, Terry.
Well, then dump it.

01:14:42.019 --> 01:14:43.561
Dump it. Just give her back Leo.

01:14:43.729 --> 01:14:46.314
It sucks, but you got your business
to worry about.

01:14:46.482 --> 01:14:48.858
Yeah, I do. Maybe you're right.
Incoming, dude.

01:14:49.526 --> 01:14:51.235
Mike.
Hey, pal.

01:14:51.403 --> 01:14:55.323
Do you know she wants to take Leo back?
Yeah, I know. She just told me today.

01:14:55.491 --> 01:14:57.742
You're not gonna let her do that,
are you?

01:14:58.702 --> 01:15:00.495
I don't know, Kyle. It's complicated.

01:15:00.662 --> 01:15:02.163
What's complicated?

01:15:02.331 --> 01:15:05.124
She doesn't give a shit about him.
You can't let her do that.

01:15:05.292 --> 01:15:09.795
All right. Why don't you just go get ready
for practice, all right? I'll deal with it.

01:15:11.423 --> 01:15:12.757
Fine.

01:15:13.217 --> 01:15:16.010
But I told her I'm staying with you guys
until I leave.

01:15:16.929 --> 01:15:18.221
Stay focused, Kyle.

01:15:22.434 --> 01:15:25.269
What's your play?
Well, I have no fricking idea.

01:15:26.772 --> 01:15:28.731
She's looking for a payout, dude.

01:15:28.899 --> 01:15:30.942
Just give her an exit.
What does that mean?

01:15:31.109 --> 01:15:34.487
Give her some of Leo's money and
send her home. He's not gonna miss it.

01:15:34.655 --> 01:15:38.491
No, I can't do that.
She's not even in his-

01:15:40.536 --> 01:15:44.121
That's right, she's not. And she
doesn't know it, and that's my play.

01:15:44.289 --> 01:15:46.082
Wait, what's your play?

01:15:49.545 --> 01:15:52.505
Don't worry about it.
Can you get practice started?

01:15:52.673 --> 01:15:56.259
Really? Yeah.
Good, go.

01:15:56.426 --> 01:15:59.136
Want me to slap you, get you psyched?
No, I really don't.

01:16:00.264 --> 01:16:03.474
I know that we're all concerned
with what's best for Leo...

01:16:03.642 --> 01:16:06.769
...so I'm hoping that we can
settle this in an amicable way.

01:16:06.937 --> 01:16:08.145
Well, so do we.
Good.

01:16:08.313 --> 01:16:13.317
Well, um, to that end, I thought that
I would lay all the cards on the table...

01:16:13.485 --> 01:16:18.322
...so that maybe you can understand why
I'm hesitating in turning Leo over to Cindy.

01:16:18.865 --> 01:16:20.408
Okay.

01:16:21.201 --> 01:16:23.494
Okay.

01:16:24.997 --> 01:16:29.584
Cindy, your father disinherited you
from his will, completely.

01:16:29.751 --> 01:16:33.921
And I'm afraid that that can't change
now that he's been declared incapacitated.

01:16:35.507 --> 01:16:37.008
What?

01:16:37.926 --> 01:16:39.260
Is that true?

01:16:39.428 --> 01:16:41.679
We'll have to see a copy of the will, Mike.

01:16:41.847 --> 01:16:44.932
Certainly. I brought you a copy.

01:16:45.100 --> 01:16:46.726
Thank you.
You bet.

01:16:47.352 --> 01:16:49.562
Then who did he leave it to? Kyle?

01:16:49.730 --> 01:16:51.689
No.
Then who? You?

01:16:51.857 --> 01:16:52.898
No, no.

01:16:53.066 --> 01:16:55.651
He actually left it
to the municipal parks system.

01:16:55.819 --> 01:16:58.112
He wanted the town park
dedicated in his name.

01:17:00.198 --> 01:17:03.284
Oh, my God. He is such a scumbag.

01:17:03.619 --> 01:17:06.829
Okay.
Oh, my God. No.

01:17:07.247 --> 01:17:11.667
He never cared about a fucking thing except
himself and his goddamn fucking money!

01:17:11.835 --> 01:17:13.210
Cindy.
Oh, my God!

01:17:13.378 --> 01:17:15.546
Don't do this.
Oh, God, I can't believe this.

01:17:15.714 --> 01:17:17.548
Please.
"Please" what?

01:17:17.716 --> 01:17:18.716
"Please"?

01:17:18.884 --> 01:17:21.719
I need to discuss this with my client.
Understood.

01:17:21.887 --> 01:17:24.722
Discuss? I'm not taking care of him
if I'm not getting anything.

01:17:24.890 --> 01:17:26.223
That's it. No!
Stop it.

01:17:26.725 --> 01:17:29.185
Oh, my God.
Uh, we're finished here, Mike.

01:17:29.353 --> 01:17:31.812
Understand completely.
I'm gonna leave that with you.

01:17:32.147 --> 01:17:33.731
Thank you.

01:17:35.025 --> 01:17:37.693
How did you not know this?
Look. Calm down.

01:17:37.861 --> 01:17:39.779
What the fuck were you doing?

01:17:46.870 --> 01:17:48.746
Brass balls, buddy. Brass balls.

01:17:48.914 --> 01:17:51.165
Yeah, and she's moved back to the motel.
Good.

01:17:51.333 --> 01:17:54.293
Yes, it is. I think it worked.
It totally worked.

01:17:54.461 --> 01:17:57.088
They opened their kimono
and you made them eat the trade.

01:17:57.255 --> 01:17:59.548
I don't know what you're talking about.
Really?

01:17:59.716 --> 01:18:01.300
No, no, really.

01:18:11.978 --> 01:18:13.688
It's time, coach.

01:18:14.856 --> 01:18:18.109
Hey, you ready?

01:18:22.823 --> 01:18:24.699
He's ready.

01:18:31.081 --> 01:18:34.291
This is exciting, huh?
You think there are scouts here?

01:18:34.459 --> 01:18:37.128
Definitely. Wait till we get to the states.
Atlantic City?

01:18:37.295 --> 01:18:39.213
Oh. We're gonna have so much fun.
Fierce.

01:18:39.881 --> 01:18:40.965
Good luck, baby.

01:18:51.059 --> 01:18:52.685
Lockup.

01:18:53.270 --> 01:18:55.604
Okay. Listen up, all right?

01:18:55.772 --> 01:18:57.648
One more win and we go to the states.

01:18:57.816 --> 01:19:00.151
That's all that matters,
that's all that counts.

01:19:00.318 --> 01:19:01.944
Hey! Listen to me.

01:19:03.155 --> 01:19:05.197
You stay in this, okay?

01:19:05.365 --> 01:19:09.618
This is your place.
This is your place, you control it.

01:19:09.786 --> 01:19:11.829
Remember? You control it!

01:19:12.414 --> 01:19:13.748
Now, go get him! Finish it!

01:19:13.915 --> 01:19:17.626
At 119, we have Timmons,
New Providence...

01:19:18.003 --> 01:19:19.670
...and Brown, Saddle Brook.

01:19:25.761 --> 01:19:27.428
Ready to go on the whistle, kid.

01:19:27.596 --> 01:19:29.680
Here we go.
Okay, we're ready.

01:19:30.098 --> 01:19:31.640
Good game, gentlemen.

01:19:31.808 --> 01:19:34.018
Stance.
Come on, Kyle, you got this.

01:19:36.188 --> 01:19:38.063
Head up! Head up! Head up!

01:19:42.402 --> 01:19:44.779
Kyle!
That's a point, right?

01:19:44.946 --> 01:19:47.406
Yo, what do you got?
Unsportsmanlike conduct.

01:19:47.574 --> 01:19:50.201
Kyle! Control. Settle down.
One point, red.

01:19:50.577 --> 01:19:54.538
Just settle down, okay?
Let's go, Chris!

01:20:03.089 --> 01:20:05.341
Sprawl!
Sprawl, Kyle! Sprawl!

01:20:06.510 --> 01:20:08.385
Foot's on the mat. On the mat.
On the mat.

01:20:09.971 --> 01:20:11.222
Settle down.

01:20:12.182 --> 01:20:15.434
No, that's it. Over. Over.

01:20:34.788 --> 01:20:36.372
How you doing?

01:20:38.625 --> 01:20:40.251
I'm sorry.

01:20:42.337 --> 01:20:46.757
Hey. It's all right, man. It's all right.

01:20:56.685 --> 01:20:59.103
I don't wanna go with her, Mike.

01:20:59.646 --> 01:21:01.272
I don't.

01:21:04.150 --> 01:21:05.943
Okay, pal.

01:21:07.445 --> 01:21:09.280
Okay.

01:21:25.589 --> 01:21:27.798
Hey, buddy. Heads up.

01:21:29.551 --> 01:21:32.553
Take them to the car, would you?
I'll be right there.

01:21:36.808 --> 01:21:41.061
Why are you here?
I wanted to see my son wrestle.

01:21:41.229 --> 01:21:46.150
Yeah, well, your son had a pretty good
chance to do something special in there.

01:21:46.401 --> 01:21:48.027
Maybe even change his life.

01:21:48.194 --> 01:21:50.321
And that's gone now,
so I hope you're happy.

01:21:50.655 --> 01:21:52.948
That's not my fault.
It isn't?

01:21:53.491 --> 01:21:56.076
Why do you think he lost his shit
in there today? Huh?

01:21:56.703 --> 01:21:59.288
What do you want?
I want my father.

01:22:00.665 --> 01:22:02.833
It didn't sound like that the other day.

01:22:03.168 --> 01:22:06.003
You have no idea what my father
used to be like.

01:22:06.171 --> 01:22:07.963
He was different.

01:22:08.131 --> 01:22:12.009
He treated me like shit.
So you're gonna return the favor, is that it?

01:22:12.177 --> 01:22:13.510
I want that commission!

01:22:14.012 --> 01:22:15.888
That's mine!
Is that what this is about?

01:22:16.056 --> 01:22:18.641
Fifteen hundred dollars? My God.

01:22:18.808 --> 01:22:20.351
Isn't that why you took him?

01:22:31.613 --> 01:22:33.864
Okay. You know what, I'll tell you what.

01:22:34.032 --> 01:22:37.534
You want the commission?
Fine, I will let you have it.

01:22:37.702 --> 01:22:39.161
You don't even have to take Leo.

01:22:39.329 --> 01:22:42.247
I will take care of him for free,
and I will send you the check.

01:22:42.415 --> 01:22:44.208
On one condition.

01:22:44.626 --> 01:22:48.045
What's that?
That you leave Kyle here with us...

01:22:48.213 --> 01:22:50.214
...until he finishes high school.

01:22:51.383 --> 01:22:54.635
I'm his mother. He belongs with me.

01:22:54.803 --> 01:22:56.387
You sure he feels that way?

01:22:56.554 --> 01:22:58.722
Don't you tell me what my son feels.

01:22:58.890 --> 01:23:01.558
He's coming with me,
and there isn't anything you can do.

01:23:01.726 --> 01:23:03.394
Then you can't have that commission.

01:23:03.561 --> 01:23:05.562
Oh, well, we'll see about that!

01:23:05.730 --> 01:23:07.523
Yeah, we will.

01:23:09.234 --> 01:23:10.901
I want to see my son!

01:23:11.444 --> 01:23:14.321
Give him a call. You got his number.

01:23:21.496 --> 01:23:23.580
We were right there, Mike.

01:23:23.915 --> 01:23:25.749
Right fucking there.

01:23:27.085 --> 01:23:28.919
Now we got nothing.

01:23:40.682 --> 01:23:42.224
Are you okay?

01:23:44.352 --> 01:23:45.769
No.

01:23:47.480 --> 01:23:50.274
Mike. Your mom's here.
Dinner's almost ready.

01:23:50.442 --> 01:23:52.443
You seen Kyle?
He's not in the basement?

01:23:52.610 --> 01:23:54.278
No.
For chrissake.

01:23:55.363 --> 01:23:58.282
I'll find him.
Thanks, Terry.

01:23:58.450 --> 01:24:00.868
What a day, huh?
Yeah, right.

01:24:06.624 --> 01:24:07.666
You okay?

01:24:10.128 --> 01:24:11.670
What are we gonna do?

01:24:11.838 --> 01:24:16.300
There's nothing to do. I can't stop her.
She's gonna take Leo and Kyle with her.

01:24:16.468 --> 01:24:19.386
You don't think you can beat her in court?
No, I don't. Nope.

01:24:19.554 --> 01:24:22.639
Well, isn't it obvious
she just wants him for the money?

01:24:25.060 --> 01:24:27.394
I just can't win this one, Jack.

01:24:27.562 --> 01:24:28.979
Trust me.

01:24:29.939 --> 01:24:31.732
I do.

01:24:39.908 --> 01:24:42.034
Hey, Kyle. Honey, come in.

01:24:43.661 --> 01:24:45.662
I'm so glad you came.

01:24:48.541 --> 01:24:50.250
Have a seat, honey.

01:24:51.002 --> 01:24:53.170
You want a soda or something?

01:24:53.546 --> 01:24:55.255
What do you want?
Ahem.

01:25:04.224 --> 01:25:08.352
I just wanted to say
how sorry I was about the match.

01:25:09.646 --> 01:25:12.314
Is that why you called?
Just to tell me that?

01:25:13.983 --> 01:25:15.484
No.

01:25:16.027 --> 01:25:21.448
I also wanted to say that I'll do
whatever you think is best for Leo.

01:25:21.616 --> 01:25:23.200
I promise.

01:25:23.368 --> 01:25:25.327
Then leave him here, where he is.

01:25:26.663 --> 01:25:31.125
I have to tell you, I'm not sure
that's what Leo wants.

01:25:31.876 --> 01:25:33.377
Here.

01:25:36.381 --> 01:25:38.882
Just read the parts in yellow.
What is it?

01:25:39.050 --> 01:25:41.510
It's the transcript
from when Leo was in court.

01:25:41.928 --> 01:25:43.846
My lawyer got it for me.

01:25:46.808 --> 01:25:47.850
This isn't real.

01:25:48.017 --> 01:25:50.686
The judge told Leo he had to live there.
No.

01:25:50.854 --> 01:25:52.980
No, honey. This is official from the court.

01:25:53.481 --> 01:25:55.149
That's what Mike said.

01:25:56.276 --> 01:26:00.070
He gets paid
for being Leo's guardian, Kyle.

01:26:00.738 --> 01:26:04.366
And then he just put him in that place
so he wouldn't have to deal with him.

01:26:04.534 --> 01:26:06.702
Leo belongs with us.

01:26:07.120 --> 01:26:08.162
Why?

01:26:10.540 --> 01:26:14.001
Because we deserve that money, Kyle.
Not some lawyer.

01:26:15.253 --> 01:26:19.047
You're a big boy.
You can understand that.

01:26:23.511 --> 01:26:25.721
Look, Kyle, honey-

01:26:27.223 --> 01:26:30.100
Shut up. Just shut up.

01:26:30.685 --> 01:26:33.103
I don't care about any of this.
Just leave Leo alone!

01:26:34.105 --> 01:26:35.606
Do you hear me?

01:26:35.940 --> 01:26:37.482
Do you?

01:26:43.656 --> 01:26:45.949
Thanks, Karen. I appreciate it.

01:26:46.117 --> 01:26:47.367
Yeah, bye.

01:26:47.535 --> 01:26:49.494
Anything?
No, he's not at Stemler's.

01:26:49.662 --> 01:26:51.205
Where could he be?
I don't know.

01:26:51.372 --> 01:26:53.707
Uh, maybe he went for a walk.
We should take a drive.

01:26:53.875 --> 01:26:55.125
Your mom can stay with the kids.

01:26:56.544 --> 01:26:59.254
Where we gonna go? Hold on. Yes?

01:26:59.422 --> 01:27:01.006
Hello?

01:27:01.382 --> 01:27:03.634
Yeah, this is him.
Who is it?

01:27:05.220 --> 01:27:06.637
What?

01:27:07.055 --> 01:27:09.056
It has been a very long day.

01:27:09.224 --> 01:27:10.515
I need some answers.

01:27:10.683 --> 01:27:13.644
Now, if you can't give them to me,
get me somebody who can.

01:27:13.978 --> 01:27:15.562
Now.
Sir, please stay calm.

01:27:15.730 --> 01:27:17.731
We're doing our best.
You've lost my ward.

01:27:17.899 --> 01:27:19.358
Calm down.
We'll find him.

01:27:19.525 --> 01:27:21.443
"Calm down"?
We're gonna sue your ass.

01:27:21.611 --> 01:27:23.946
I'm sorry.
How could you just let him escape?

01:27:24.113 --> 01:27:26.698
Look, he's definitely
not on the premises.

01:27:26.866 --> 01:27:29.618
A lot of the time,
they just try to go home.

01:27:29.786 --> 01:27:33.705
We're about to go there now.
Unbelievable. Unbelievable.

01:27:33.873 --> 01:27:36.833
Hey, folks,
keep an eye on each other.

01:27:37.001 --> 01:27:38.502
Terry.

01:27:45.593 --> 01:27:47.928
The lights are on.
It's gotta be him.

01:27:48.096 --> 01:27:50.764
Hey, did you bring the key?
No, I forgot it.

01:27:55.061 --> 01:27:57.062
My bad, my bad, my bad.

01:27:57.230 --> 01:27:59.690
Ring the bell.
I just did, sweetheart, okay?

01:28:01.526 --> 01:28:04.027
I think I hear a TV.
Really?

01:28:04.654 --> 01:28:07.656
You're right. Okay.

01:28:08.950 --> 01:28:10.158
Hold on, hold on.

01:28:11.077 --> 01:28:13.370
Hold on.

01:28:18.835 --> 01:28:20.836
Yes, there he is.
What's he doing?

01:28:21.004 --> 01:28:22.296
He's watching TV.

01:28:29.012 --> 01:28:30.637
He's not responding. Hit the bell.

01:28:32.181 --> 01:28:33.724
Anything?
Nothing.

01:28:33.891 --> 01:28:36.560
Dude, is he dead?
I have no fricking idea.

01:28:36.728 --> 01:28:39.187
Christ.
Dude, this is kind of spooky.

01:28:39.355 --> 01:28:40.772
Should we break in?
No.

01:28:40.982 --> 01:28:43.692
Okay. I've got a key back at the office.
I'll go get it.

01:28:43.860 --> 01:28:45.652
You guys stay here.
Alone?

01:28:52.285 --> 01:28:53.910
Come on in.

01:28:55.121 --> 01:28:57.331
Super spooky.
You go first.

01:28:57.498 --> 01:29:00.083
Oh, for God's sake.
I'll go last.

01:29:08.551 --> 01:29:10.344
You okay, Leo?

01:29:12.764 --> 01:29:14.639
How'd you get here, pal?

01:29:16.267 --> 01:29:17.768
Leo, did you walk here?

01:29:19.437 --> 01:29:21.355
I brought him.
Aah!

01:29:22.899 --> 01:29:25.192
You brought him?
Yeah.

01:29:25.360 --> 01:29:28.111
Are you out of your mind?
We've been worried sick about him.

01:29:28.279 --> 01:29:29.529
About both of you.

01:29:29.697 --> 01:29:32.157
You didn't have to worry about us.

01:29:34.786 --> 01:29:36.995
Really creepy. Just saying.

01:29:40.124 --> 01:29:43.210
What the hell are you doing?
Making spaghetti.

01:29:43.378 --> 01:29:46.463
Jesus, have you lost your mind?
No.

01:29:46.631 --> 01:29:50.008
You can't just take him out of the home.
This is where he belongs.

01:29:50.176 --> 01:29:53.220
No, honey, he needs to be at Oak Knoll.
We talked about this.

01:29:53.763 --> 01:29:55.389
Yeah, we did.

01:29:55.556 --> 01:29:57.265
I remember.

01:29:57.433 --> 01:29:59.184
Listen to this.

01:29:59.477 --> 01:30:02.229
"Mr. Flaherty:
Mr. Poplar wants to live at home.

01:30:03.231 --> 01:30:05.315
Judge Lee: You can do that, Mike?

01:30:05.483 --> 01:30:08.902
Mr. Flaherty: Yes, I can. Really."

01:30:09.070 --> 01:30:10.946
What? What is this? What?

01:30:11.781 --> 01:30:13.115
It's true, isn't it?

01:30:14.450 --> 01:30:15.575
Mike?

01:30:16.994 --> 01:30:18.829
What is this?

01:30:22.166 --> 01:30:24.167
You're just like her.

01:30:24.961 --> 01:30:26.253
Mike.

01:30:30.007 --> 01:30:34.511
Hey, Kyle. Hey,
will you hold on a second?

01:30:34.679 --> 01:30:35.971
Don't touch me!

01:30:37.849 --> 01:30:40.434
I'm sorry, come on.
I said, don't touch me!

01:30:40.601 --> 01:30:42.853
Jesus. Okay.

01:30:43.020 --> 01:30:45.564
Let me explain, okay?
Explain what?

01:30:45.731 --> 01:30:48.108
How you lied to me?
How you lied to Leo?

01:30:48.276 --> 01:30:51.236
No, that's not how it was, okay?
Then how was it, Mike?

01:30:51.404 --> 01:30:54.030
Calm down. All right? Come on, man.

01:30:54.198 --> 01:30:55.782
Calm down.
Watch the head fake.

01:30:55.950 --> 01:30:57.826
I'm not gonna wrestle with you.

01:30:57.994 --> 01:30:59.703
Hands up, hands up.
Stop it, okay?

01:30:59.871 --> 01:31:01.413
Don't egg him on.
That's not helping.

01:31:01.581 --> 01:31:03.707
It is. This kid's a good wrestler.
Calm down.

01:31:03.875 --> 01:31:05.584
You see, I told you.
Stop it!

01:31:05.751 --> 01:31:08.879
Okay, buddy, get to your base. Good.
Stop!

01:31:09.046 --> 01:31:10.714
Mike, stop it!
Okay, buddy.

01:31:10.882 --> 01:31:13.383
I'm trying to stop it!
Sit out, Mike!

01:31:13.551 --> 01:31:15.886
Sit out!
Would you stop coaching and break it up?

01:31:16.053 --> 01:31:17.971
Ow. Get the hell off me!
Break it up!

01:31:19.515 --> 01:31:22.100
Come on, get up. It's okay.
I- No, no, no.

01:31:22.268 --> 01:31:24.561
I'm just the ref. I'm just the ref!
Just the ref!

01:31:27.565 --> 01:31:29.733
Come on!
Kyle!

01:31:34.322 --> 01:31:36.198
Is this true, Mike?

01:31:36.365 --> 01:31:37.866
Did you say this to the judge?

01:31:39.911 --> 01:31:41.578
Yeah, I did.

01:31:43.206 --> 01:31:45.916
So then why did you move him
if he wanted to stay here?

01:31:46.876 --> 01:31:50.837
Because it would have been
too much work to leave him here.

01:31:51.005 --> 01:31:52.589
Okay? I couldn't handle it.

01:31:53.132 --> 01:31:56.176
Then you shouldn't have taken him.
I had to do it, all right?

01:31:56.344 --> 01:32:00.597
Why?
Because I needed the money. Okay?

01:32:00.765 --> 01:32:02.098
We need the money.

01:32:02.266 --> 01:32:06.019
So you took some old man
out of his home to make money off him?

01:32:06.187 --> 01:32:08.939
What, are you out of your freaking mind?
No. No!

01:32:09.148 --> 01:32:12.609
I did not think that it would
get this complicated, okay?

01:32:12.985 --> 01:32:16.905
Really? Or you just didn't think
you'd get caught?

01:32:26.999 --> 01:32:30.627
Jack, where you going?
Home!

01:32:44.809 --> 01:32:46.768
Incoming call. Do you copy?

01:32:46.936 --> 01:32:52.065
Incoming call. Charlie Squadron taking
heavy fire. Requesting air strike Bravo.

01:32:52.984 --> 01:32:54.609
Do you copy?

01:32:54.777 --> 01:32:57.612
Delta Squad, disengage target.

01:33:00.992 --> 01:33:02.659
Hello, Mom?

01:33:06.664 --> 01:33:09.291
Did your mom just crank-call you?

01:33:09.792 --> 01:33:11.084
No.

01:33:12.962 --> 01:33:16.006
So did you and coach get into a fight
because you lost?

01:33:16.173 --> 01:33:18.300
No, we got in a fight
because he's an asshole.

01:33:19.468 --> 01:33:22.345
Really?
Yeah, really, Stem.

01:33:23.598 --> 01:33:25.640
Well, I'm sure he'll
make it up to you, bro.

01:33:25.808 --> 01:33:27.642
You're the best wrestler he's ever had.

01:33:28.311 --> 01:33:31.146
I mean, he's always been cool to me,
and I suck.

01:33:38.362 --> 01:33:41.031
Hi, Leo.
Hey.

01:33:42.199 --> 01:33:46.161
I fell asleep. Ahem. I'm sorry.

01:33:46.579 --> 01:33:48.038
Sorry for what?

01:33:55.546 --> 01:33:56.796
Wanna go home, Leo?

01:33:59.008 --> 01:34:01.885
Yes. I'd like that.

01:34:15.483 --> 01:34:18.693
Where's Kyle?
He slept at Stemler's.

01:34:18.861 --> 01:34:22.614
You?
Uh, Oak Knoll.

01:34:26.535 --> 01:34:28.370
So, what are you gonna do?

01:34:29.246 --> 01:34:30.872
I have to go to court.

01:34:31.040 --> 01:34:33.583
No, you can't. You told the judge
you were keeping Leo at home.

01:34:34.168 --> 01:34:35.293
I know.

01:34:35.461 --> 01:34:38.296
Tell her you changed your mind
and he needs to be in a home.

01:34:38.464 --> 01:34:39.923
No one could argue with that.

01:34:40.925 --> 01:34:42.425
I can't do that.

01:34:43.594 --> 01:34:47.263
Why not?
Because it's not true.

01:34:48.182 --> 01:34:50.684
Oh, well, I'm glad you're done lying now.

01:34:51.602 --> 01:34:54.854
Just in time to lose your practice.
That's how your family survives.

01:34:55.022 --> 01:34:56.773
Did you ever think of that, Mike?

01:34:57.775 --> 01:34:59.859
Yeah, all the time.

01:35:05.950 --> 01:35:07.784
I'm sorry, Jack.

01:35:08.285 --> 01:35:10.203
I really am.

01:35:12.790 --> 01:35:14.457
I know.

01:35:26.137 --> 01:35:28.888
Hey, pal. How'd you get down here?

01:35:29.265 --> 01:35:32.517
The window.
You hungry? I'm making pancakes.

01:35:32.685 --> 01:35:34.602
I'm leaving. I just came to get my shit.

01:35:34.770 --> 01:35:37.021
Right now?
Yeah.

01:35:40.484 --> 01:35:42.068
Hey, Kyle.

01:35:43.028 --> 01:35:44.738
Listen, I just wanna say I'm sorry.

01:35:44.905 --> 01:35:47.741
I know, Mike, you're sorry.
Everyone's always sorry.

01:35:48.159 --> 01:35:52.328
I'm moving Leo back home, Kyle, and I'm
gonna fight to make sure that he stays there.

01:35:52.496 --> 01:35:55.707
It's too late, you'll lose.
My mother's gonna take him.

01:35:55.875 --> 01:35:58.752
Maybe, but I'm still gonna try.

01:35:58.919 --> 01:36:02.338
So what? You want me to forgive you now,
is that it, Mike?

01:36:03.674 --> 01:36:07.260
No, I just want you
to give me another chance.

01:36:15.019 --> 01:36:17.228
This is bullshit!

01:36:18.814 --> 01:36:22.525
Hey, Kyle, listen-
I want to be alone.

01:36:22.693 --> 01:36:26.488
What?
I just wanna be down here alone.

01:36:26.864 --> 01:36:29.991
Okay. All right. Yeah.

01:36:34.580 --> 01:36:37.624
Kyle, I just wanna say we love you.

01:37:40.396 --> 01:37:41.729
Hey, guys.
Hey.

01:37:41.897 --> 01:37:44.023
Hey, Mr. Poplar.
Good to see you.

01:37:44.191 --> 01:37:45.233
Jackie.
Hey.

01:37:45.401 --> 01:37:47.402
How's it going?
What are you doing here?

01:37:47.570 --> 01:37:49.571
Dude, I'm your assistant coach.

01:37:49.738 --> 01:37:51.614
Just notice who isn't here.
Aha.

01:38:03.335 --> 01:38:05.378
Ah. Hey, Mike?

01:38:05.921 --> 01:38:07.046
Hey, Eleanor.

01:38:07.339 --> 01:38:08.590
Can I talk to you?

01:38:09.133 --> 01:38:12.719
Sure. Hold on, okay?

01:38:19.435 --> 01:38:22.770
You know the transcript alone
is enough to hang you.

01:38:22.938 --> 01:38:25.899
Yeah, well, we'll see what happens.

01:38:27.026 --> 01:38:29.736
Shame on you, counselor.

01:38:33.574 --> 01:38:35.116
Is that it?

01:38:36.285 --> 01:38:38.661
No, my client would like to talk to you.

01:38:52.927 --> 01:38:54.844
Is your deal still available?

01:38:57.139 --> 01:38:58.598
What about Kyle?

01:39:00.684 --> 01:39:02.518
He can stay.

01:39:05.022 --> 01:39:06.856
Then, yes, it is.

01:39:07.733 --> 01:39:09.150
And you'll send me the checks?

01:39:10.277 --> 01:39:11.694
Every month.

01:39:14.281 --> 01:39:15.823
You take good care of him?

01:39:16.533 --> 01:39:18.326
We will.

01:39:20.537 --> 01:39:21.829
I wanna say goodbye.

01:39:23.290 --> 01:39:24.791
Okay.

01:39:25.709 --> 01:39:28.753
Kyle, come here for a minute.

01:39:32.216 --> 01:39:34.717
Your mom wants to talk to you
for a minute.

01:40:07.042 --> 01:40:08.334
Nice shot.
Thanks.

01:40:08.502 --> 01:40:10.753
Not bad, not bad.
Check this out.

01:40:10.921 --> 01:40:12.422
All right.

01:40:14.550 --> 01:40:17.093
Nice, dude.
This mallet's crap.

01:40:24.018 --> 01:40:25.059
Hey, guys.

01:40:25.227 --> 01:40:27.103
Hi, Daddy. I'm winning.
That's great.

01:40:27.271 --> 01:40:28.646
What up, coach?
Hey, Stemler.

01:40:28.814 --> 01:40:31.357
Kyle, can you move those
garbage cans around the side?

01:40:31.525 --> 01:40:32.942
All right.
Thanks, pal.

01:40:33.110 --> 01:40:35.111
All right, I'm switching colors.
Why?

01:40:35.279 --> 01:40:36.696
I'm not feeling the orange.

01:40:36.864 --> 01:40:38.948
Hey, honey.
Hey. How was work?

01:40:39.116 --> 01:40:42.952
Good. I got stuck at the office with a client.
I know, Shelly called.

01:40:43.120 --> 01:40:46.080
I dropped off the fan at Leo's today.
Thanks for doing that.

01:40:46.248 --> 01:40:48.458
I'll be right back down.
You got time to eat?

01:40:48.625 --> 01:40:51.627
Uh, I'll eat there.
All right, make sure you do.

01:41:04.349 --> 01:41:07.852
Hey, barkeep.
I will take a banana daiquiri, please.

01:41:08.020 --> 01:41:11.064
All right.
Would you like an umbrella with that?

01:41:11.231 --> 01:41:13.316
No, thank you, but keep those coming.

01:41:15.903 --> 01:41:18.946
So how you doing, pal?
Me?

01:41:19.740 --> 01:41:21.115
I'm pretty good.

01:41:32.753 --> 01:41:38.257
I was driftin', cryin'

